expression: text
---
Print statistics about trees in a btrfs filesystem

Reads the filesystem image or block device directly (no mount required). By
default prints statistics for the root, extent, checksum, and fs trees. Use -t
to restrict to a single tree.

When the filesystem is mounted the numbers may be slightly inaccurate due to
concurrent modifications.

Usage: tree-stats [OPTIONS] <DEVICE>

Arguments:
  <DEVICE>
          Path to a btrfs block device or image file

Options:
  -b, --raw
          Print sizes in raw bytes instead of human-readable form

  -t, --tree <TREE>
          Only print stats for the given tree (name or numeric ID)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
